20between%20tasks%2C%20which%20have%20a%20narrowly%20defined%20process%20and%20outcome%2C%20and%20jobs%2C%20which%20are%20a%20collection%20of%20tasks.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAI%20won't%20generally%20replace%20jobs%2C%20these%20people%20said%2C%20but%20it%20will%20absolutely%20automate%20tasks.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETake%20someone%20who%20works%20in%20recruitment.%20Maybe%20their%20job%20involves%20paperwork%2C%20identifying%20and%20meeting%20with%20candidates%2C%20and%20providing%20strategic%20counsel%20to%20employers%20and%20prospective%20employees.%20The%20paperwork%20can%20most%20likely%20be%20heavily%20automated%2C%20potentially%20freeing%20up%20that%20recruiter%20for%20more%20human-to-human%20interactions.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EBig%20savings%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDeb%20Cupp%2C%20the%20president%20of%20Microsoft%20Americas%2C%20said%20in%20a%20panel%20discussion%20that%20the%20software%20giant%20saved%20%24100%20million%20in%20its%20customer-service%20operation%20by%20implementing%20AI.%20Similarly%2C%20Mihir%20Shukla%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20Automation%20Anywhere%2C%20said%20the%20company%20cut%20customer-service%20costs%20by%2040%25%20while%20seeing%20improved%20performance%20since%20introducing%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWorkforce%20concerns%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20whenever%20there's%20talk%20of%20cost%20savings%20and%20increased%20productivity%2C%20there's%20understandable%20concern%20that%20this%20is%20code%20for%20job%20losses.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20is%20an%20equal%20measure%20of%20excitement%20and%20wanting%20to%20engage%20with%20it%20and%20nervousness%20about%20what%20it's%20going%20to%20do%20for%20them%20and%20their%20jobs%2C%26quot%3B%20Tanuj%20Kapilashrami%2C%20the%20chief%20human%20resources%20officer%20at%20Standard%20Chartered%2C%20said%20of%20employees%20and%20AI%20on%20one%20panel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20recent%20survey%20found%20that%2051%25%20of%20global%20executives%2C%2050%25%20of%20global%20CEOs%2C%20and%2052%25%20of%20US%20CEOs%20said%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwill-ai-replace-jobs-generative-artificial-intelligence-tools-training-ceos-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ejob%20replacement%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20could%20be%20one%20of%20the%20effects%20of%20adopting%20AI%20in%20their%20businesses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAna%20Kreacic%2C%20the%20chief%20knowledge%20officer%20at%20Oliver%20Wyman%2C%20said%20that%20in%20some%20cases%2C%20productivity%20was%20actually%20declining%20because%20workers%20were%20paralyzed%20by%20their%20fear%20of%20the%20technology.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EReskilling%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20means%20it%20will%20be%20crucial%20to%20find%20ways%20to%20retrain%20workers%20for%20the%20human%20tasks%20that%20are%20still%20necessary%20in%20the%20AI%20era.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20Automation%20Anywhere%2C%20which%2C%20as%20its%20name%20suggests%2C%20works%20on%20automating%20work%2C%20the%20customer-service%20team%20shrank%20when%20AI%20was%20implemented.%20But%20some%20of%20those%20customer-service%20agents%20found%20new%20roles%20at%20the%20company%2C%20either%20in%20customer%20success%20or%20in%20technical%20roles%2C%20based%20on%20their%20transferable%20skills.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShukla%20said%20the%20business%20world%20had%20defined%20roles%20increasingly%20narrowly%20as%20companies%20looked%20to%20industrialize%20their%20operations%20and%20scale.%20In%20the%20age%20of%20AI%2C%20the%20workforce%20will%20be%20more%20fluid%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecky%20Frankiewicz%2C%20the%20chief%20commercial%20officer%20at%20ManpowerGroup%2C%20echoed%20this%2C%20saying%20the%20age%20of%20the%20static%20job%20is%20over%2C%20and%20employees%20will%20have%20to%20continually%20upskill%20and%20reskill%20in%20the%20future.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20means%20employers%20should%20look%20for%20potential%20hires%20who%20are%20adaptable%20and%20have%20the%20ability%20to%20learn%20quickly%20rather%20than%20focus%20on%20specific%20skills%20that%20could%20soon%20be%20redundant.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EFrom%20small%20to%20scale%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%202023%20was%20the%20year%20of%20the%20pilot%20study%2C%20then%202024%20will%20be%20the%20year%20of%20operationalizing%20AI%2C%20Lareina%20Yee%2C%20a%20senior%20partner%20at%20McKinsey%2C%20told%20me.%20Others%20I%20spoke%20to%20agreed%3A%20Many%20businesses%20have%20small-scale%20AI%20experiments%20running%2C%20often%20with%20promising%20results%20so%20far.%20The%20challenge%20is%20in%20taking%20that%20pilot%20and%20specific-use%20case%20and%20scaling%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EDifferent%20models%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-create-ai-materials-resources-guide-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELLM%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20(large%20language%20model)%20might%20have%20been%20up%20there%20with%20WEF%20as%20the%20acronym%20of%20Davos%202024%2C%20many%20of%20those%20I%20spoke%20to%20stressed%20the%20difficulties%20with%20multipurpose%20models%20trained%20on%20giant%20datasets%20like%20OpenAI's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-gpt4-ai-model-got-lazier-dumber-chatgpt-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGPT-4%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20many%20cases%2C%20the%20most%20effective%20AI%20tools%2C%20particularly%20for%20corporate%20use%2C%20are%20those%20that%20have%20narrowly%20defined%20purposes%20and%20have%20been%20trained%20or%20fine-tuned%20on%20exclusive%2C%20bespoke%20datasets.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20McKinsey%20built%20an%20AI%20tool%20that's%20trained%20on%20the%20consulting%20firm's%20rich%20archive%20of%20PowerPoint%20presentations%2C%20white%20papers%2C%20and%20Excel%20spreadsheets%20and%20helps%20consultants%20get%20up%20to%20speed%20on%20specific%20topics%20more%20quickly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20will%20be%20different%20classes%20of%20models%20for%20different%20contexts%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Satish%20H.C.%2C%20an%20EVP%20and%20cohead%20of%20delivery%20at%20Infosys.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ECost%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20there's%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmark-zuckerberg-ai-flex-meta-nvidia-gpus-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecost%3C%2Fa%3E%20involved.%20These%20AI%20projects%20are%20expensive%2C%20and%20not%20every%20company%20has%20the%20financial%20or%20human%20capital%20to%20pursue%20an%20ambitious%20AI%20strategy.%20Plus%2C%20not%20every%20AI%20project%20will%20generate%20a%20positive%20return%20on%20investment%2C%20especially%20when%20factoring%20in%20not%20just%20the%20cost%20of%20the%20tech%20itself%20but%20the%20costs%20of%20changing%20workflows%20and%20retraining%20staff.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EAugmentation%20%E2%80%A6%20for%20now%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20always%20a%20few%20buzzwords%20that%20emerge%20at%20every%20Davos%2C%20and%20augmentation%20was%20one%20of%20those%20this%20time%20around.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20idea%20is%20simple%3A%20Rather%20than%20replacing%20humans%2C%20AI%20will%20superpower%20them%2C%20taking%20on%20some%20of%20the%20most%20boring%20and%20repetitive%20tasks%20and%20freeing%20them%20up%20for%20higher-level%20work.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20machines%20get%20better%20at%20being%20machines%2C%20humans%20can%20get%20better%20at%20being%20humans%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Kapilashram%20from%20Standard%20Chartered.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20certainly%20seems%20to%20be%20supported%20by%20the%20research%20so%20far.%20But%20some%20questioned%20how%20long%20that%20could%20last.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-deepmind-ai-could-run-businesses-in-five-years-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EMustafa%20Suleyman%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20cofounder%20of%20the%20AI%20pioneer%20DeepMind%20who%20now%20runs%20the%20startup%20Inflection%20AI%2C%20predicted%20that%20AI%20will%20be%20so%20business%20savvy%20by%202030%20that%20it%20may%20be%20capable%20of%20acting%20like%20an%20entrepreneur%2C%20mini%20project%20manager%2C%20or%20inventor%20by%20manufacturing%2C%20marketing%2C%20and%20selling%20products%20for%20profit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20going%20to%20have%20not%20just%20those%20capabilities%2C%20but%20those%20capabilities%20widely%20available%20for%20very%20cheap%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20that%20completely%20changes%20the%20economy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20a%20panel%20where%20Kapilashram%20was%20speaking%2C%20Azeem%20Azhar%2C%20who%20writes%20the%20Exponential%20View%20newsletter%2C%20noted%20that%20when%20AI-powered%20game%20engines%20emerged%2C%20the%20hybrid%20of%20human%20players%20plus%20AI%20outperformed%20for%20about%20eight%20years.%20Now%2C%20though%2C%20the%20AI%20game%20player%20wins%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDan%20Vahdat%2C%20the%20founder%20and%20CEO%20of%20Huma%20Therapeutics%2C%20said%20that%20while%20we%20might%20think%20of%20empathy%20as%20a%20distinctly%20human%20characteristic%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjamanetwork.com%2Fjournals%2Fjamainternalmedicine%2Farticle-abstract%2F2804309%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eresearch%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20published%20last%20year%20showed%20that%20patients%20found%20AI%20chatbots%20to%20be%20more%20empathetic%20in%20their%20communication%20than%20medical%20professionals.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20few%20final%20words%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20computer%20scientist%20Roy%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-stocks-enter-correction-territory-chart-analysis-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EAmara%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20often%20credited%20with%20first%20saying%20that%20we%20overestimate%20the%20impact%20of%20a%20technology%20in%20the%20short%20term%20and%20underestimate%20its%20impact%20in%20the%20long%20term.%20AI%20will%20likely%20be%20no%20different.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdavos-global-elite-saying-about-ai-behind-closed-doors-2024-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705702521000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65aae74edcdb354a98595071%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdavos-global-elite-saying-about-ai-behind-closed-doors-2024-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20AI%20era%20at%20Davos%202024%3A%20Copilots%2C%20task%20automation%2C%20workforce%20reskilling%2C%20and%20human%20augmentation.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22mturner%40businessinsider.com%20(Matt%20Turner)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A32%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdavos-global-elite-saying-about-ai-behind-closed-doors-2024-1%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Green%20Day%20Previews%20New%20Album%20%E2%80%98Saviors%E2%80%99%20at%20Intimate%2C%20Hit-Filled%20Irving%20Plaza%20Show%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705702500000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F1943777578-e1705675604510.jpg%3Fw%3D1000%26h%3D563%26crop%3D1%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F%3Fp%3D1235877769%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22On%20Aug.%205%2C%20Green%20Day%20will%20play%20for%20more%20than%2040%2C000%20people%20at%20New%20York%E2%80%99s%20Citi%20Field.%20But%20before%20that%2C%20the%20alt-rock%20trio%20treated%201%2C200%20fans%20in%20the%20city%20to%20an%20intimate%20gig%20at%20Irving%20Plaza%2C%20where%20they%20previewed%20songs%20off%20their%20new%20record%2C%20%E2%80%9CSaviors%2C%E2%80%9D%20and%20celebrated%20milestone%20anniversaries%20of%20their%20most%20famous%20albums%3A%20