%20are%20mainly%20heirs%20who%20do%20not%20actively%20run%20a%20company%2C%20and%20therefore%20feel%20uncomfortable%20with%20great%20wealth%20that%20they%20have%20not%20generated%20themselves%2C%E2%80%9D%20explained%20Stefan%20Bach%20from%20the%20German%20Institute%20for%20Economic%20Research%20(DIW)%20in%20Berlin.%20%E2%80%9CBut%20they%20tend%20to%20be%20isolated%20voices.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fworlds-richest-five-men-double-wealth-oxfam%2Fa-67979934%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3Evast%20majority%20of%20the%20super-rich%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0were%20more%20reserved%20in%20this%20regard.%20Indeed%2C%20there%20was%20strong%20political%20resistance%20from%20business%20associations%2C%20which%2C%20thanks%20to%20their%20work%20with%20lobby%20groups%2C%20were%20generally%20well-connected%20to%20high-ranking%20politicians.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CMany%20large%20fortunes%20are%20also%20tied%20up%20in%20business%2C%E2%80%9D%20Bach%20said.%20The%20idea%2C%20business%20associations%20argue%2C%20is%20that%20low%20taxes%20for%20entrepreneurs%20provide%20incentives%20to%20invest%20and%20create%20jobs%2C%20meaning%20higher%20taxes%20could%20jeopardize%20jobs%20and%20investment%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0and%20potentially%20even%20lead%20to%20company%20heirs%20choosing%20not%20to%20run%20the%20company%20they%20could%20inherit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20argument%20essentially%20stifles%20all%20possible%20political%20debates%20on%20wealth%20or%20inheritance%20taxes%2C%E2%80%9D%20Bach%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EEurope%E2%80%99s%20shift%20to%20the%20right%20makes%20change%20unlikely%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGenerally%2C%20it%20does%20not%20make%20sense%20for%20a%20country%20to%20act%20alone%20when%20imposing%20taxes%20on%20large%20fortunes.%20%E2%80%9CBigger%2C%20international%20companies%20and%2C%20of%20course%2C%20the%20super-rich%20all%20play%20to%20the%20tune%20of%20international%20law%2C%E2%80%9D%20continued%20Bach%2C%20explaining%20that%20billionaires%20could%20easily%20relocate%20to%20other%20countries%20with%20more%20favourable%20tax%20legislation.%20%E2%80%9CNothing%20is%20gained%20if%2C%20in%20the%20end%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20only%20the%20well-behaved%20German%20small%20and%20medium-sized%20companies%20that%20get%20fleeced%20because%20they%20remain%20loyal%20to%20their%20country.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20he%20pointed%20out%20that%20generating%20more%20income%20for%20state%20coffers%20through%20a%20balanced%20combination%20of%20tax%20increases%C2%A0on%20the%20top%20income%20bracket%20or%20with%20a%20wealth%20tax%20was%20possible.%20%E2%80%9CBut%2C%20of%20course%2C%20this%20can%20only%20be%20done%20in%20a%20way%20that%20is%20coordinated%20internationally%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20there%20had%20been%20some%20successful%20attempts%20to%20curb%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Ftaxes%2Ft-19021286%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3Etax%20evasion%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0by%20large%20corporations%20in%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOver%20130%20countries%2C%20which%20together%20account%20for%2090%25%20of%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20economic%20output%2C%20had%20also%20agreed%20on%20a%20max%2C%20and%20in%20so%20doing%20were%20trying%20to%20prevent%20companies%20from%20just%20moving%20onto%20other%20countries%20with%20better%20tax%20rates.%20Last%20year%2C%20several%20EU%20lawmakers%20proposed%20a%20similar%20global%20minimum%20tax%20on%20extremely%20high%20private%20wealth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20Bach%20doubted%20that%20there%20would%20be%20any%20developments%20on%20this%20front%20in%20the%20near%20future%2C%20and%20this%20was%20partly%20to%20do%20with%20the%20general%20shift%20to%20the%20right%20across%20Europe.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20are%20hardly%20any%20left-wing%20majorities%20left%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said%2C%20explaining%20that%20when%20it%20came%20to%20tax%20measures%2C%20it%20was%